{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_0186jVmMbzPVgS765ehckJ8j","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→PRIZM_VERSION: 1.0\n     2→PROJECT: PrizmClaw\n     3→LANG: JavaScript (ESM), Node.js 22\n     4→DESCRIPTION: Telegram → AI CLI bridge with web admin panel; bidirectional sync, pipeline orchestration\n     5→ENTRY: src/index.js\n     6→TEST_CMD: node --test tests/**/*.test.js\n     7→\n     8→MODULE_INDEX:\n     9→- src -> .prizm-docs/src/\n    10→- src/adapters -> .prizm-docs/src/adapters.prizm\n    11→- src/bot -> .prizm-docs/src/bot.prizm\n    12→- src/http -> .prizm-docs/src/http.prizm\n    13→- src/pipeline-infra -> .prizm-docs/src/pipeline-infra.prizm\n    14→- src/routes -> .prizm-docs/src/routes.prizm\n    15→- src/security -> .prizm-docs/src/security.prizm\n    16→- src/services -> .prizm-docs/src/services.prizm\n    17→- src/utils -> .prizm-docs/src/utils.prizm\n    18→- public -> (static web panel assets — no L1 doc)\n    19→\n    20→RULES:\n    21→- All chat messages route through messageRouter.processMessage() — never call executeAiCli directly for chat\n    22→- Session keys: bound sessions use telegram:{chatId}, unbound web sessions use web:{sessionId}\n    23→- Safe-to-modify config keys: LOG_LEVEL, REQUEST_TIMEOUT_MS, AI_CLI_HEARTBEAT_MS, MAX_PROMPT_CHARS, MAX_HISTORY_TURNS, SYSTEM_MONITOR_INTERVAL_MS, SESSION_TIMEOUT_MS, TASK_DEBOUNCE_MS\n    24→- ANSI stripping happens in onAssistantChunk hook via ansiProcessChunk() — never strip in final reply path\n    25→- .btn:disabled uses pointer-events: none to prevent hover CSS from firing on disabled buttons\n    26→- .panel and .sub-panel are separate CSS rules (not grouped) to allow different box-shadow depths; shadow colors use rgba derived from --text (#1f2633) for cool-tone palette coordination\n    27→\n    28→UPDATED: 2026-03-23\n    29→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"dd0fcd73-259f-4cfb-b510-593052b16cf1","uuid":"fd3b998d-2877-44d6-8cd3-aab9898a1259","timestamp":"2026-03-22T16:59:50.411Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/.prizm-docs/root.prizm","content":"PRIZM_VERSION: 1.0\nPROJECT: PrizmClaw\nLANG: JavaScript (ESM), Node.js 22\nDESCRIPTION: Telegram → AI CLI bridge with web admin panel; bidirectional sync, pipeline orchestration\nENTRY: src/index.js\nTEST_CMD: node --test tests/**/*.test.js\n\nMODULE_INDEX:\n- src -> .prizm-docs/src/\n- src/adapters -> .prizm-docs/src/adapters.prizm\n- src/bot -> .prizm-docs/src/bot.prizm\n- src/http -> .prizm-docs/src/http.prizm\n- src/pipeline-infra -> .prizm-docs/src/pipeline-infra.prizm\n- src/routes -> .prizm-docs/src/routes.prizm\n- src/security -> .prizm-docs/src/security.prizm\n- src/services -> .prizm-docs/src/services.prizm\n- src/utils -> .prizm-docs/src/utils.prizm\n- public -> (static web panel assets — no L1 doc)\n\nRULES:\n- All chat messages route through messageRouter.processMessage() — never call executeAiCli directly for chat\n- Session keys: bound sessions use telegram:{chatId}, unbound web sessions use web:{sessionId}\n- Safe-to-modify config keys: LOG_LEVEL, REQUEST_TIMEOUT_MS, AI_CLI_HEARTBEAT_MS, MAX_PROMPT_CHARS, MAX_HISTORY_TURNS, SYSTEM_MONITOR_INTERVAL_MS, SESSION_TIMEOUT_MS, TASK_DEBOUNCE_MS\n- ANSI stripping happens in onAssistantChunk hook via ansiProcessChunk() — never strip in final reply path\n- .btn:disabled uses pointer-events: none to prevent hover CSS from firing on disabled buttons\n- .panel and .sub-panel are separate CSS rules (not grouped) to allow different box-shadow depths; shadow colors use rgba derived from --text (#1f2633) for cool-tone palette coordination\n\nUPDATED: 2026-03-23\n","numLines":29,"startLine":1,"totalLines":29}}}
